text: Bertrand de Five Pranger (born May 28, 1950 in Barcelona) is a swimmer from Spain. He had a disability. He raced at the 1972 Summer Paralympics. He came in second in two different swimming races. He raced at the 1976 Summer Paralympics. He came in first in one swimming race and second in a different swimming race. == References == Category:Spanish swimmers Category:Living people Category:1950 births Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Spain Category:Paralympic gold medalists for Spain Category:Sportspeople from Barcelona Category:1972 Summer Paralympics Category:1976 Summer Paralympics
